  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators aim to assess the dental status of psychiatric patients suffering from
      severe mental illness (schizophrenia, bipolar disorder, ptsd, resistant depression).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      PATIENTS WILL BE ASSESSED USING THE

      1. DMFT (Decayed/Missing/Filled teeth)

      AN EPIDEMILOGICAL ASSESSMENT TOOL THAT ASSESSES:

        1. THE NUMBER OF TEETH WITH CURRENT DECAY

        2. THE NUMBER OF TEETH MISSING

        3. THE NUMBER OF TEATH TREATED IN THE PAST (FILLED)

      2. CPI - Community Periodontal Index AN ASSESSMENT OF THE GUMS

      3. OHIP-Oral Health Impact Profile A SELF-RATING FORM TO ASSESS THE SOCIAL AND FUNCTIONAL
      AFECTS OF THIER DENTAL STATUS
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
